This Project is about Servlets and JSP


A)Servlets

a)Controller - 

0)Servlet Mapping is to map servlets with request URL, can be done @WebServlet
1)To process request and response. Methods in servlets doGet() and doPost().   
2)You can get data from getParameter("") method.
3)Interact with other servlets through sendRedirect and RequestDispatcher.
4)Store data in request and forward through RequestDispatcher.
5)URL rewriting is another method to store data and pass to another page.
6)Using session to store data and using sendRedirect().
7)Cookie to store data in client side.
8)PrintWriter to print data on client side.

b)Views - To show data and interact with user

0)Simple HTML pages or JSP pages (Make Dynamic Web Content)
1)Scriplet Tag to write scripts - main code.
2)Declarative Tag to declare variables.

 

c)Models - To make referenced data types. 





